explanation: This solution iterates through all numbers from 1 to n, checks if each number is a factor of n, and keeps track of the count. When the count reaches k, it returns the current number as the kth factor. If n has less than k factors, it returns -1. The time complexity is O(sqrt(n)) because we only need to iterate up to the square root of n to find all factors.

